clue: This word for a large system of stars comes from the Greek for "milk"

response: a galaxy

clue: Noted astronomer Fred Whipple famously defined a comet as an enormous, dirty one of these

response: a snowball

clue: Algol is one of these, 2 stars revolving around each other, also called a double star

response: a binary (system)

clue: A faint constellation in the northern sky, Camelopardalis represents this animal

response: the giraffe

clue: The Oort Cloud & its inner region, this belt, are thought to contain billions of comets

response: the Kuiper Belt

